<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-819-898  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 819 898.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Sept 1990 v15 n9 p324(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Byte summit: the software anchor.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The gap between hardware and software capabilities is discussed bya group of computer industry executives, analysts, observers, andinnovators.andP;  Opinions are widely scattered as to whether there isin fact a gap.andP;  Many of the contributors feel that the gap isnon-existent, and one individual maintains that software isactually outstripping hardware.andP;  Those who believe the gap doesexist attribute it variously to software development processes orto the fact that software is written for hardware, rather thanhardware being developed to run software.andP;  It is also generallyacknowledged that software is simply more difficult to developthan hardware.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software DesignAnalysisMethods.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>